transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, this is Olivia speaking.

Speaker 2: Who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 1: Hello.

Speaker 2: Hi.

Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, this is Olivia speaking.

Speaker 2: Who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 1: This is Olivia.

Speaker 2: Les Bryant.

Speaker 1: Hi, Les.

Speaker 2: How are you?

Speaker 1: I'm doing good.

Speaker 2: I'm so glad to hear that.

Speaker 1: How can I help you today, Les?

Speaker 2: I bought a product in January, and it looks like you guys have billed me again for the same product, or you put me in a subscription, which I did not get into.

Speaker 1: Yeah, I can help you with this.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Les, what is your date of birth?

Speaker 2: 1/13/1971.

Speaker 1: Great. And you're located at 8711 Grant Line Road, Elk Grove, California?

Speaker 2: That's correct.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so I see you here.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so if you don't want to receive regular monthly refills with the prescription, you certainly don't have to.

Speaker 1: You always have the option to place your prescription on hold for up to six months at a time, just because six months is when the prescription would expire.

Speaker 2: If we didn't refill it, and the way that would work is whenever you are ready to order, if it is before then you can, you just have to give us a call to place the order yourself.

Speaker 1: Okay, and then the one you're trying to fill now, you can cancel that one, right?

Speaker 2: So that one is showing me as delivered because it was placed six days ago.

Speaker 1: Let me pull up the USPS tracking number so I can see when it was delivered, and I can just confirm your address with you.

Speaker 2: You know, I never signed up for a subscription, so why does it automatically do that?

Speaker 1: Yeah, so when you place the order online, a Terms of Service screen popped up, and at the bottom of it it said your prescription will come with refills. If you want to change or address them in any way, call this phone number, and it provided the phone number to us.

Speaker 2: And because we didn't hear from you, and because you ordered 10 pills as the original prescription, you did do the add-ons.

Speaker 1: You got 20, right?

Speaker 2: So it makes sense that you haven't used 20 pills in a month.

Speaker 1: But because your original prescription was for 10, the pharmacy usually approves 10 pills to be a monthly refill.

Speaker 2: So that is why you received that refill.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Well, it's over now, right? There won't be any more billing?

Speaker 1: Yes. I am placing the prescription on hold for you.

Speaker 2: So if you need anything before the middle of August, just give us a call.

Speaker 1: We're always here Monday through Friday, 8 to 5 Pacific.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: Thank you.

Speaker 2: Thank you. Bye.

Speaker 1: Yep, bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
